        public XMLOptions withRowLabels()
        Description copied from class: BaseIOOptions
        Returns a new T with row labels enabled. When exporting, this means that labels assigned to the Rows in the exported Table will be included in the output. When importing, this means that row labels assigned to the data in the import file will be assigned to the Rows read from the file.
        Overrides:
        withRowLabels in class BaseIOOptions<XMLOptions>
        Returns:
        a new T with row labels enabled

      • withRowLabels

        public XMLOptions withRowLabels(boolean b)
        Description copied from class: BaseIOOptions
        Returns a new T with row labels enabled or disabled, as per the supplied parameter b. When exporting, this means that when enabled, labels assigned to the Rows in the exported Table will be included in the output. When disabled, row labels in the exported table are ignored and are not included in the output. When importing, this means that when enabled, row labels assigned to the data in the import file will be assigned to the Rows read from the file.
        Overrides:
        withRowLabels in class BaseIOOptions<XMLOptions>
        Parameters:
        b - true to include Row labels, false to ignore them
        Returns:
        a new T with row labels enabled or disabled

      • withIgnoreEmptyRows

        public XMLOptions withIgnoreEmptyRows(boolean b)
        Description copied from class: BaseIOOptions
        Sets the behavior this T uses to handle empty rows. When set to true, empty rows in the source Table are ignored (not written to the output file). On import, empty rows in the source file are ignored. When set to false, empty rows are included in the exported file, in a file-format-appropriate manner. On import, empty Rows are inserted into the new Table when encountered in the imported file.
        Overrides:
        withIgnoreEmptyRows in class BaseIOOptions<XMLOptions>
        Parameters:
        b - true to import/export empty Rows, false to ignore them
        Returns:
        a new T where empty rows are or are not ignored
